        <bioghist id="ref8" encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Historical Note</head>
            <p>The Swiss Exhibition for Women's Work (SAFFA) was an exhibition organized by the
                major national women's organizations in Switzerland. The first SAFFA exhibition was
                in held in Bern, 1928. The theme was to show the importance of female contributions
                to the social and economic activities in Switzerland at the time. A second
                exhibition was held in Zurich, 1958 focusing on "women in the family, occupation and
                state." These exhibitions were organized and produced entirely by women and the
                exhibition buildings for SAFFA 58 were designed and built by Swiss women
                architects.</p>
            <p/>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1" encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>Collection consists of sixty-three drawings of the buildings for the Swiss fair
                including the collaborative work of Claire Rufer-Eckmann, Beate Billeter, Verena
                Fuhrimann, Jetti Judin-Mutzenberg, and Annemarie Hubacher-Constam.</p>
        </scopecontent>
